OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHalifax apologises after   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Finterest rate email blunder
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Halifax has said sorry after it sent   
OL,6, emails to customers incorrectly saying 
OL,7, that the Bank of England had raised    
OL,8, interest rates.                        
OL,10,FSome mortgage customers received a     
OL,11,Fmessage on Tuesday saying "the Bank of 
OL,12,FEngland base rate has changed today".  
OL,14,FBut the decision by the central bank on
OL,15,Fwhether or not to raise interest rates 
OL,16,Fis not due until Thursday lunchtime.   
OL,18,FThe lender followed up with a second   
OL,19,Femail later, apologising to customers  
OL,20,Ffor "any confusion" caused.            
